**GlobalEduERP Build**
- Created Web API skeleton with Swagger metadata and controller routing (`GlobalEduERP/Program.cs`).
- Added 30 domain classes covering admissions, learning, finance, research, and alumni needs (`GlobalEduERP/Models/DomainModels.cs`).
- Seeded in-memory sample data for quick testing (`GlobalEduERP/Data/InMemoryData.cs`).
- Implemented feature controllers: admissions (apps/students), learning (courses/curricula/research), and alumni (profiles/donations/grants) under `GlobalEduERP/Controllers/`.
- Authored full relational SQL schema for all entities (`GlobalEduERP/SQL/schema.sql`).

Next steps
1) Run `dotnet restore` (network access required) then `dotnet run` from `LCP-Vibe-7/GlobalEduERP` to exercise the API.
2) Expand controllers with POST/PUT flows and validation if you want persistence beyond the seed data.
3) Hook the SQL schema up with EF Core or your DB of choice when packages are available.
